oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Interview - Frank Liddell - 2014-08-02
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Frank Liddell has produced five Miranda Lambert albums and was the Academy of Country Music's 2012 Producer of the Year. As founder and president of Carnival Music, Liddell published the first #1 hits by songwriters Scooter Carusoe, Natalie Hemby, Troy Jones, David Nail, and Bruce Robison. Texas native Liddell also has produced acclaimed albums by Brandi Carlile, Jack Ingram, Chris Knight, David Nail, Kellie Pickler, Pistol Annies, and Lee Ann Womack (whom he married in 1999). Presented in support of the exhibition Miranda Lambert: Backstage Access.
